        <desc>
            <p>Banksy went to New Orleans on the third anniversary of the Hurricane Katherina disaster. There are possibly eleven stencils in New Orleans from this period, among them the iconic Nola. The stencil on a petrol station in Alabama of a hooded Ku Klux Klan member was quickly removed.</p>
